Package bank

Class Branch

java.lang.Object
bank.Branch
public class Branch extends Object
Branch class will be used to store and access branch information e.g. location, code, opening and closing hours. The class has methods which work hand-in-hand with the Bank it will be attached to, to display information and perform financial transactions.

  • Constructor Details

    • Branch

      public Branch(int branchCode)
      Branch constructor takes in a specific id of the branch code and obtains necessary data from Branch.csv. It displays the values of each attribute that a branch has and segregates them by individual branch code for loop is used for assigning the attributes of the branch class from the array Buffered Reader is scans through the Branch.csv for the following variables:

      branchCode holds the ID of the Branch

      branchName holds the name of the Branch

      branchReserve holds the Branch's reserve

      openingHours holds the opening hours of a Branch

      closingHours holds the closing hours of a Branch

      Parameters:
      branchCode - represents the unique identifier of the branch
